## Approach

### Threat status assessment

The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species Categories and Criteria are used to assess the threat status of species.

Categorisation of southern African anostracan species and their conservation status was attempted by [@hamer1997a] and [@roeck2007a], according to the IUCN criteria at that time. From their attempts, only four species were officially added to the IUCN Red list, because many species lacked information to be properly categorised and fully assessed. Considerable advances have been made in anostracan research in South Africa over the past few decades. In 2023, the first comprehensive assessment of South African Anostraca was initiated through the NRF FBIP Project REFRESH. This assessment was conducted through online workshops by experts from multiple institutions. From the 40 species that were assessed, 36 have been published, with four assessments still in process.

About species threat status: See details about how the IUCN Red List assessments are conducted [here](../integrated-findings/chl_spl_explained.qmd).

